snippet.textDisplay: These new Ozzy songs, especially this one, are almost hard to watch.  Im 53, grew up with Sabbath, Ozzy and that era.  Ive seen Ozzy multiple times in concert.  On one hand, I love his heavier music.  On the other, some of this new stuff is some of the best.  BUT, what saddens me is there is a deep undertone to this of saying goodbye.  I know OZ has had med issues and all in recent years, and it's well documented that he probably is a medical wonder surviving the substances over the years. And Of course, he is aging as the rest of us.   I get all that, I see it and all, but hard to hear someone recording what sounds like goodbye letters.   Be well OZ!  Thank you for so much great music!!!!  Also, the song itself resonates with me deeply.  Again, Im 53, health issues, Mom/dad/only brother and my only son are all gone.  I struggle with my mortality alot anymore as I had such big dreams and all, and feel Ive achieved so little.  So, the song itself speaks to me deeply as well.  tear jerker

snippet.textDisplay:
Some bits about this video / song that absolutely stand out:

'Don't forget me as the colours fade
When the lights go down, it's just an empty stage...'

We all hope to be remembered, in some way even after all is said and done. But, eventually, we'll leave this mortal coil and the stage, whichever stage we set will be left empty for whatever comes next - if it does at all. Our stage is set.

When I first saw this video, my first reaction was: 'This is the end'.

Then of course the scene with Randy and Ozzy's reaction - his death is still raw and it pains him and you can see that in interviews past - the one where he's being played that unheard solo on the video with Jack in it - and Ozzy's reaction: 'He died'. How can you not feel that emotion and pain that you saw - and it's real. And that orchestral backing ... WHO is that?! I got So Tired vibes from this whole video and song - the orchestra, guitar, vocals, piano (because I love that song and I truly think this could be Ozzy's finest song in a long time). If the album had this at the end with those strings fading out, wow.

snippet.textDisplay: This song made me very emotional, the video tear me down. When he's gone I'm gonna cry for him so bad. I see him like a far distant loving relative. Like an uncle or something like that. The power of his music and his legacy, his story, his way to do things, the tv show, all made part of my life growing old until this very day. I didn't know how much I loved this man that I don't personally know until this lyrics and video. This is just a reminder that you can impact a life even if you are not aware of. God bless his soul and his family. We should all live by his way, always doing what we love and being loving with our family.
